        "answer_count": 1,
        "title": "The package org.sqlite conflicts with a package accessible from another module: sqlite.jdbc in eclipse",
        "body": "<p>The following error displayed on <strong>JDBC.java<\/strong> file while inserting data in sqlite database:<\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>\"The <strong>package org.sqlite<\/strong> conflicts with a package accessible from another module: <strong>sqlite.jdbc<\/strong>\"<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<pre><code>package org.sqlite;\n\nimport java.sql.Connection;    \nimport java.sql.Driver;    \nimport java.sql.DriverPropertyInfo;    \nimport java.sql.SQLException;    \nimport java.sql.SQLFeatureNotSupportedException;    \nimport java.util.Properties;    \nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\n\npublic class JDBC implements Driver {\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p><strong>How to avoid this error?<\/strong><\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 58281138,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "eclipse"
        ],
        "score": 1,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 4663,
        "last_edit_date": 1570517064
    },
    "question_comments": [],
    "answers": [{
        "owner": {
            "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/FgNJn.jpg?s=256",
            "account_id": 8692823,
            "user_type": "registered",
            "user_id": 6505250,
            "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6505250/howlger",
            "reputation": 35045,
            "display_name": "howlger"
        },
        "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
        "score": 2,
        "is_accepted": false,
        "last_activity_date": 1570524372,
        "creation_date": 1570524372,
        "body": "<p>Java does <strong>not allow<\/strong> to have the <strong>same package in more than one module<\/strong>.<\/p>\n\n<p>To avoid this error do one of the following:<\/p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Rename your package<\/strong> and make sure to choose a unique name (e.g. <code>com.my_company.db_connector<\/code>)<\/li>\n<li>Do not use the Java Platform Module System (JPMS) by deleting the <code>module-info.java<\/code> file and move the <code>sqlite<\/code> JAR from the modulepath to the classpath<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n",
        "answer_id": 58282956,
        "question_id": 58281138
    }],
